        <h1>LeetCode 3650: Find Minimum Operations to Make All Elements Equal (C++)</h1>

        <div class="problem-description">
            <p><strong>Problem:</strong>
                You are given an array nums of n integers. In one operation, you can increment or decrement any element by 1. Return the minimum number of operations needed to make all elements of the array equal.
            </p>
            <p><strong>Example:</strong>
                Input: nums = [1,2,3]<br/>
                Output: 2<br/>
                Explanation: We can make all elements equal to 2 in 2 operations: Decrement nums[2] by 1, nums becomes [1,2,2]. Increment nums[0] by 1, nums becomes [2,2,2].<br/><br/>
                Input: nums = [1,5,2,3]<br/>
                Output: 5<br/>
                Explanation: We can make all elements equal to 2 or 3. To make all elements 2: 1 operation for 5-&gt;2, 1 operation for 3-&gt;2, 1 operation for 1-&gt;2. Total = 3 + 1 + 1 = 5.<br/><br/>
                Input: nums = [10,10,10]<br/>
                Output: 0<br/>
                Explanation: All elements are already equal.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="code-container">
            <button class="copy-button" onclick="copyCode(this)">Copy Code</button>
            <pre><code class="language-cpp">class Solution {
public:
    int minOperations(vector&lt;int&gt;&amp; nums) {
        // Sort the array
        sort(nums.begin(), nums.end());
        
        int n = nums.size();
        
        // The optimal target is the median
        int median = nums[n / 2];
        
        int operations = 0;
        for (int num : nums) {
            operations += abs(num - median);
        }
        
        return operations;
    }
};</code></pre>
